to the editor david e alburger letter dec 30 proposes to render everyone on board a hijacked plane temporarily unconscious by using an anesthetic gas through pipes poked through the fuselage an anesthetic that can produce mass unconsciousness without individual tight fitting masks is not yet discovered in the almost impossible scenario that this can be achieved death or severe brain damage due to lack of monitoring and life support is the only outcome for the passengers the crew and their captors fikry b salib md stamford conn dec 30 1999 the writer is associate chief of anesthesiology at stamford hospital

